.TH "SIDEMANTIC" "1" "" "Sidemantic 0.10.2" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
sidemantic \- SQL\-first semantic layer
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B
sidemantic [OPTIONS] COMMAND [ARGS]...
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Sidemantic: SQL\-first semantic layer
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-version\fR
Show version
.TP
\fB\-\-project, \-p PATH\fR
Project root (defaults to discovery from cwd)
.TP
\fB\-\-config, \-c PATH\fR
Path to config file (sidemantic.yaml)
.TP
\fB\-\-format table|csv|json|jsonl\fR
Output format for structured results
.TP
\fB\-\-plain\fR
Stable undecorated tabular output
.TP
\fB\-\-quiet, \-q\fR
Suppress non\-essential status
.TP
\fB\-\-verbose, \-v\fR
Show detailed diagnostics
.TP
\fB\-\-debug, \-d\fR
Show tracebacks for unexpected errors
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-color\fR
Disable terminal color
.TP
\fB\-\-pager, \-\-no\-pager\fR
Page long human\-readable output when writing to a terminal
.TP
\fB\-\-install\-completion\fR
Install completion for the current shell.
.TP
\fB\-\-show\-completion\fR
Show completion for the current shell, to copy it or customize the installation.
.SH "SIDEMANTIC HELP"
.SS SYNOPSIS
.B
sidemantic help [[COMMAND]...]
.SS DESCRIPTION
.PP
Show top\-level help or help for a command path.
.SH "SIDEMANTIC INFO"
.SS SYNOPSIS
.B
sidemantic info [OPTIONS] [[DIRECTORY]]
.SS DESCRIPTION
.PP
Show quick info about the semantic layer.
.PP
Examples: sidemantic info sidemantic info ./models
.SS OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-json\fR
Emit semantic\-layer metadata as JSON
.SH "SIDEMANTIC REWRITE"
.SS SYNOPSIS
.B
sidemantic rewrite [OPTIONS] SQL
.SS DESCRIPTION
.PP
Rewrite semantic SQL to ordinary SQL without executing it.
.PP
Examples: sidemantic rewrite "SELECT orders.revenue FROM orders" \-\-models ./models sidemantic rewrite "SELECT orders.revenue FROM orders" \-\-models ./models \-\-engine rust
.SS OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-models, \-m PATH\fR
Directory containing semantic layer files
.TP
\fB\-\-connection TEXT\fR
Database connection string (sets SQL dialect)
.TP
\fB\-\-db PATH\fR
Path to DuckDB database file
.TP
\fB\-\-engine TEXT\fR
Runtime engine: python, rust, or auto
.TP
\fB\-\-fallback, \-\-no\-fallback\fR
Allow Rust engine fallback to Python
.TP
\fB\-\-use\-preaggregations\fR
Enable automatic pre\-aggregation routing
.SH "SIDEMANTIC CONVERT"
.SS SYNOPSIS
.B
sidemantic convert [OPTIONS] [[SOURCE]]
.SS DESCRIPTION
.PP
Convert semantic definitions through the shared format registry.
.SS OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-output, \-o PATH\fR
Destination file or directory
.TP
\fB\-\-from TEXT\fR
Source format (default: auto\-detect)
.TP
\fB\-\-source\-extension TEXT\fR
File extension for stdin input when a format supports multiple syntaxes (for example, .sql)
.TP
\fB\-\-to TEXT\fR
Destination format
.TP
\fB\-\-force\fR
Allow writing to an existing destination
.SH "SIDEMANTIC QUERY"
.SS SYNOPSIS
.B
sidemantic query [OPTIONS] SQL
.SS DESCRIPTION
.PP
Execute a SQL query and output results as CSV.
.PP
Examples: sidemantic query "SELECT revenue FROM orders" sidemantic query "SELECT * FROM orders" \-\-output results.csv sidemantic query "SELECT * FROM orders" \-\-models ./models sidemantic query "SELECT revenue FROM orders" \-\-connection "postgres://localhost:5432/db" sidemantic query "SELECT revenue FROM orders" \-\-db data.duckdb sidemantic query "SELECT revenue FROM orders" \-\-dry\-run sidemantic query "SELECT revenue FROM orders" \-\-use\-preaggregations \-\-dry\-run
.SS OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-models, \-m PATH\fR
Directory containing semantic layer files
.TP
\fB\-\-output, \-o PATH\fR
Output file (default: stdout)
.TP
\fB\-\-connection TEXT\fR
Database connection string (e.g., postgres://host/db, bigquery://project/dataset)
.TP
\fB\-\-db PATH\fR
Path to DuckDB database file (shorthand for duckdb:/// connection)
.TP
\fB\-\-dry\-run\fR
Show generated SQL without executing
.TP
\fB\-\-engine TEXT\fR
Runtime engine: python, rust, or auto
.TP
\fB\-\-fallback, \-\-no\-fallback\fR
Allow Rust engine fallback to Python
.TP
\fB\-\-use\-preaggregations\fR
Enable automatic pre\-aggregation routing
.SH "SIDEMANTIC EXPLAIN"
.SS SYNOPSIS
.B
sidemantic explain [OPTIONS] SQL
.SS DESCRIPTION
.PP
Explain semantic SQL rewrite planning without executing the query.
.PP
Examples: sidemantic explain "SELECT revenue FROM orders" sidemantic explain "SELECT * FROM (SELECT revenue, status FROM orders) sq WHERE status = 'completed'" sidemantic explain "SELECT revenue, status FROM orders" \-\-use\-preaggregations sidemantic explain "SELECT revenue FROM orders" \-\-format json
.SS OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-models, \-m PATH\fR
Directory containing semantic layer files
.TP
\fB\-\-connection TEXT\fR
Database connection string (e.g., postgres://host/db, bigquery://project/dataset)
.TP
\fB\-\-db PATH\fR
Path to DuckDB database file (shorthand for duckdb:/// connection)
.TP
\fB\-\-use\-preaggregations\fR
Enable automatic pre\-aggregation routing
.TP
\fB\-\-engine TEXT\fR
Runtime engine: python, rust, or auto
.TP
\fB\-\-fallback, \-\-no\-fallback\fR
Allow Rust engine fallback to Python
.TP
\fB\-\-strict, \-\-no\-strict\fR
Fail on unsupported semantic SQL
.SH "SIDEMANTIC VALIDATE"
.SS SYNOPSIS
.B
sidemantic validate [OPTIONS] [[DIRECTORY]]
.SS DESCRIPTION
.PP
Validate semantic layer definitions.
.PP
Shows errors, warnings, and optionally detailed info.
.PP
Examples: sidemantic validate sidemantic validate ./models \-\-verbose
.SS OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-verbose, \-v\fR
Show detailed validation results
.TP
\fB\-\-engine TEXT\fR
Runtime engine: python, rust, or auto
.TP
\fB\-\-fallback, \-\-no\-fallback\fR
Allow Rust engine fallback to Python
.TP
\fB\-\-json\fR
Emit the validation report as JSON
.SH "SIDEMANTIC WORKBENCH"
.SS SYNOPSIS
.B
sidemantic workbench [OPTIONS] [[DIRECTORY]]
.SS DESCRIPTION
.PP
Interactive semantic layer workbench with SQL editor and charting.
.PP
Explore models, write SQL queries, and visualize results with interactive charts.
.PP
Examples: sidemantic workbench sidemantic workbench \-\-demo sidemantic workbench ./models \-\-db data/warehouse.db sidemantic workbench ./models \-\-connection "postgres://localhost:5432/db" uvx \-\-from 'sidemantic[workbench]' sidemantic workbench \-\-demo
.SS OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-demo\fR
Launch with demo data (multi\-format example)
.TP
\fB\-\-connection TEXT\fR
Database connection string (e.g., postgres://host/db, bigquery://project/dataset)
.TP
\fB\-\-db PATH\fR
Path to DuckDB database file (shorthand for duckdb:/// connection)
.SH "SIDEMANTIC LSP"
.SS SYNOPSIS
.B
sidemantic lsp
.SS DESCRIPTION
.PP
Start the LSP server for Sidemantic SQL dialect (.sql definition files).
.PP
This provides editor support for the Sidemantic SQL syntax (MODEL, DIMENSION, METRIC, RELATIONSHIP, SEGMENT statements). It does NOT provide general SQL language support.
.PP
Features: \- Autocompletion for MODEL, DIMENSION, METRIC, RELATIONSHIP, SEGMENT \- Context\-aware property suggestions (name, type, sql, agg, etc.) \- Validation errors from pydantic models \- Hover documentation for keywords and properties
.PP
Editor setup:
.PP
VS Code: Use a generic LSP client extension pointing to 'sidemantic lsp' Neovim: Add custom server config to nvim\-lspconfig
.PP
Examples: sidemantic lsp # Starts server on stdio
.SH "SIDEMANTIC DASHBOARD"
.SS SYNOPSIS
.B
sidemantic dashboard COMMAND [ARGS]...
.SS DESCRIPTION
.PP
Serve, validate, and type semantic dashboard specs
.SH "SIDEMANTIC DASHBOARD VALIDATE"
.SS SYNOPSIS
.B
sidemantic dashboard validate [OPTIONS] [[SPEC]]
.SS DESCRIPTION
.PP
Validate a semantic dashboard spec against loaded models.
.SS OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-models, \-m PATH\fR
Directory containing semantic layer files
.TP
\fB\-\-connection TEXT\fR
Database connection string (e.g., postgres://host/db, bigquery://project/dataset)
.TP
\fB\-\-db PATH\fR
Path to DuckDB database file (shorthand for duckdb:/// connection)
.TP
\fB\-\-use\-preaggregations\fR
Enable automatic pre\-aggregation routing while validating SQL
.TP
\fB\-\-json\fR
Emit the validation report as JSON
.SH "SIDEMANTIC DASHBOARD SERVE"
.SS SYNOPSIS
.B
sidemantic dashboard serve [OPTIONS] [[SPEC]]
.SS DESCRIPTION
.PP
Serve a dashboard spec in the official Sidemantic React UI.
.SS OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-models, \-m PATH\fR
Directory containing semantic layer files
.TP
\fB\-\-connection TEXT\fR
Database connection string (e.g., postgres://host/db, bigquery://project/dataset)
.TP
\fB\-\-db PATH\fR
Path to DuckDB database file (shorthand for duckdb:/// connection)
.TP
\fB\-\-host, \-H TEXT\fR
Host for dashboard server
.TP
\fB\-\-port, \-p INTEGER\fR
Port for dashboard server
.TP
\fB\-\-use\-preaggregations\fR
Enable automatic pre\-aggregation routing
.SH "SIDEMANTIC DASHBOARD TYPES"
.SS SYNOPSIS
.B
sidemantic dashboard types [OPTIONS]
.SS DESCRIPTION
.PP
Generate TypeScript dashboard config types from the semantic layer.
.SS OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-models, \-m PATH\fR
Directory containing semantic layer files
.TP
\fB\-\-out, \-\-output, \-o PATH\fR
TypeScript output file; defaults to stdout
.TP
\fB\-\-schema\-name TEXT\fR
Generated TypeScript schema export name
.SH "SIDEMANTIC GENERATE"
.SS SYNOPSIS
.B
sidemantic generate COMMAND [ARGS]...
.SS DESCRIPTION
.PP
Generate typed TypeScript clients from the semantic layer
.SH "SIDEMANTIC GENERATE CLIENT"
.SS SYNOPSIS
.B
sidemantic generate client [OPTIONS]
.SS DESCRIPTION
.PP
Generate a typed query\-client schema from the semantic layer.
.PP
Emits an `as const` schema (field types per model) for use with `createClient` from `sidemantic\-wasm/client`.
.SS OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-models, \-m PATH\fR
Directory or file with semantic layer definitions
.TP
\fB\-\-out, \-\-output, \-o PATH\fR
TypeScript output file; defaults to stdout
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-yaml\fR
Omit the embedded SCHEMA_YAML constant
.SH "SIDEMANTIC GENERATE SQL"
.SS SYNOPSIS
.B
sidemantic generate sql [OPTIONS] [[SOURCES]...]
.SS DESCRIPTION
.PP
Generate typed bindings for semantic SQL literals in TypeScript sources (sqlx\-style).
.PP
Emits a `GeneratedQueries` interface for use with `createSqlClient`. Each query is validated against the semantic layer (a bad reference fails the build). v1 limits: static string/template literals only (no `${}` interpolation); arbitrary SELECT expressions and min/max/derived metric value types are approximate.
.SS OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-models, \-m PATH\fR
Directory or file with semantic layer definitions
.TP
\fB\-\-out, \-\-output, \-o PATH\fR
TypeScript output file; defaults to stdout
.TP
\fB\-\-call TEXT\fR
Call name whose first string\-literal argument is semantic SQL
.SH "SIDEMANTIC MIGRATE"
.SS SYNOPSIS
.B
sidemantic migrate COMMAND [ARGS]...
.SS DESCRIPTION
.PP
Generate semantic models from SQL or check migration coverage
.SH "SIDEMANTIC MIGRATE GENERATE"
.SS SYNOPSIS
.B
sidemantic migrate generate [OPTIONS] [[QUERIES]]
.SS DESCRIPTION
.PP
Generate models and rewritten queries from SQL or warehouse history.
.SS OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-output, \-o PATH\fR
Output project root (defaults to current project)
.TP
\fB\-\-history\fR
Generate from configured warehouse query history
.TP
\fB\-\-connection TEXT\fR
Connection override for \-\-history
.TP
\fB\-\-days, \-d INTEGER\fR

.TP
\fB\-\-limit, \-l INTEGER\fR

.TP
\fB\-\-json\fR
Emit the generation report as JSON
.SH "SIDEMANTIC MIGRATE CHECK"
.SS SYNOPSIS
.B
sidemantic migrate check [OPTIONS] [[QUERIES]]
.SS DESCRIPTION
.PP
Check how well the project models cover existing SQL.
.SS OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-models, \-m PATH\fR
Models override
.TP
\fB\-\-history\fR
Check configured warehouse query history
.TP
\fB\-\-connection TEXT\fR
Connection override for \-\-history
.TP
\fB\-\-days, \-d INTEGER\fR

.TP
\fB\-\-limit, \-l INTEGER\fR

.TP
\fB\-\-verbose, \-v\fR

.TP
\fB\-\-json\fR
Emit the coverage report as JSON
.SH "SIDEMANTIC SERVER"
.SS SYNOPSIS
.B
sidemantic server COMMAND [ARGS]...
.SS DESCRIPTION
.PP
Run Sidemantic API, PostgreSQL, or MCP servers
.SH "SIDEMANTIC SERVER MCP"
.SS SYNOPSIS
.B
sidemantic server mcp [OPTIONS] [[DIRECTORY]]
.SS DESCRIPTION
.PP
Start an MCP server for the semantic layer.
.PP
Provides tools for listing models, getting model details, and running queries through the Model Context Protocol.
.PP
Examples: sidemantic server mcp sidemantic server mcp ./models \-\-db data/warehouse.db sidemantic server mcp \-\-demo sidemantic server mcp \-\-apps \-\-http \-\-port 4100
.SS OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-connection TEXT\fR
Database connection string
.TP
\fB\-\-db PATH\fR
Path to DuckDB database file (optional)
.TP
\fB\-\-init\-sql TEXT\fR
SQL statements to run after connecting (e.g., LOAD httpfs)
.TP
\fB\-\-demo\fR
Use demo data instead of a directory
.TP
\fB\-\-apps\fR
Enable interactive UI widgets (requires mcp\-ui\-server)
.TP
\fB\-\-http\fR
Use HTTP transport instead of stdio
.TP
\fB\-\-port, \-p INTEGER\fR
Port for HTTP server
.TP
\fB\-\-user\-attrs\-file PATH\fR
Path to a JSON user\-attributes object applied to every MCP query
.TP
\fB\-\-enforce\-visibility\fR
Hide and reject fields declared public: false
.SH "SIDEMANTIC SERVER POSTGRES"
.SS SYNOPSIS
.B
sidemantic server postgres [OPTIONS] [[DIRECTORY]]
.SS DESCRIPTION
.PP
Start a PostgreSQL\-compatible server for the semantic layer.
.PP
Exposes your semantic layer over the PostgreSQL wire protocol, allowing you to connect with any PostgreSQL client (psql, DBeaver, Tableau, etc.).
.PP
Examples: sidemantic server postgres \-\-port 5433 sidemantic server postgres ./models \-\-db data/warehouse.db sidemantic server postgres \-\-connection "postgres://localhost:5432/analytics" sidemantic server postgres \-\-connection "bigquery://project/dataset" \-\-port 5433 sidemantic server postgres \-\-demo sidemantic server postgres \-\-username user \-\-password\-file .secrets/pg\-password
.SS OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-demo\fR
Use demo data
.TP
\fB\-\-connection TEXT\fR
Database connection string (e.g., postgres://host/db, bigquery://project/dataset)
.TP
\fB\-\-db PATH\fR
Path to DuckDB database file (shorthand for duckdb:/// connection)
.TP
\fB\-\-host, \-H TEXT\fR
Host/IP to bind to (overrides config, default 127.0.0.1)
.TP
\fB\-\-port, \-p INTEGER\fR
Port to listen on (overrides config)
.TP
\fB\-\-username, \-u TEXT\fR
Username for authentication (overrides config)
.TP
\fB\-\-password\-file PATH\fR
Read the authentication password from a file, or \- for stdin
.TP
\fB\-\-user\-attrs\-file PATH\fR
Path to a JSON file mapping usernames \-> user\-attribute dicts for row/access security
.TP
\fB\-\-enforce\-visibility\fR
Hide and reject fields declared public: false
.SH "SIDEMANTIC SERVER API"
.SS SYNOPSIS
.B
sidemantic server api [OPTIONS] [[DIRECTORY]]
.SS DESCRIPTION
.PP
Start an HTTP API server for the semantic layer.
.PP
Exposes semantic queries over JSON or Arrow IPC for remote clients.
.PP
Examples: sidemantic server api sidemantic server api ./models \-\-db data/warehouse.db sidemantic server api \-\-connection "postgres://localhost:5432/analytics" sidemantic server api \-\-auth\-token\-file .secrets/api\-token \-\-cors\-origin https://app.example.com sidemantic server api \-\-demo
.SS OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-demo\fR
Use demo data
.TP
\fB\-\-connection TEXT\fR
Database connection string (e.g., postgres://host/db, bigquery://project/dataset)
.TP
\fB\-\-db PATH\fR
Path to DuckDB database file (shorthand for duckdb:/// connection)
.TP
\fB\-\-host, \-H TEXT\fR
Host/IP to bind to (overrides config, default 127.0.0.1)
.TP
\fB\-\-port, \-p INTEGER\fR
Port to listen on (overrides config)
.TP
\fB\-\-auth\-token\-file PATH\fR
Read the API bearer token from a file, or \- for stdin
.TP
\fB\-\-cors\-origin TEXT\fR
Allowed CORS origin (repeatable)
.TP
\fB\-\-max\-request\-body\-bytes INTEGER\fR
Maximum request body size in bytes
.TP
\fB\-\-result\-cache\-mb INTEGER\fR
Result cache size in MB (0 disables; default 0)
.TP
\fB\-\-result\-cache\-ttl FLOAT\fR
Result cache entry TTL in seconds (default 60)
.TP
\fB\-\-require\-user\-attrs\fR
Require the user\-attributes header on data endpoints (reject with 400 if missing)
.TP
\fB\-\-enforce\-visibility\fR
Reject requests for non\-public dimensions/metrics
.TP
\fB\-\-user\-header TEXT\fR
Trusted request header carrying JSON user attributes
.TP
\fB\-\-ui, \-\-no\-ui\fR
Serve the embedded web UI at the root path
.SH "SIDEMANTIC PREAGG"
.SS SYNOPSIS
.B
sidemantic preagg COMMAND [ARGS]...
.SS DESCRIPTION
.PP
Pre\-aggregation recommendation and management
.SH "SIDEMANTIC PREAGG RECOMMEND"
.SS SYNOPSIS
.B
sidemantic preagg recommend [OPTIONS]
.SS DESCRIPTION
.PP
Show pre\-aggregation recommendations based on query patterns.
.PP
Examples: sidemantic preagg recommend \-\-connection "bigquery://project/dataset" sidemantic preagg recommend \-\-db data.db \-\-min\-count 50 \-\-top 10 sidemantic preagg recommend \-\-queries queries.sql \-\-min\-score 0.5
.SS OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-queries, \-q PATH\fR
Path to file/folder with SQL queries
.TP
\fB\-\-connection TEXT\fR
Database connection string to fetch query history
.TP
\fB\-\-db PATH\fR
Path to DuckDB database file (shorthand for duckdb:/// connection)
.TP
\fB\-\-days, \-d INTEGER\fR
Days of query history to fetch (default: 7)
.TP
\fB\-\-limit, \-l INTEGER\fR
Max queries to analyze (default: 1000)
.TP
\fB\-\-min\-count INTEGER\fR
Minimum query count for recommendation (default: 10)
.TP
\fB\-\-min\-score FLOAT\fR
Minimum benefit score (0\-1, default: 0.3)
.TP
\fB\-\-top, \-n INTEGER\fR
Show only top N recommendations
.TP
\fB\-\-json\fR
Emit recommendations as JSON
.SH "SIDEMANTIC PREAGG APPLY"
.SS SYNOPSIS
.B
sidemantic preagg apply [OPTIONS] [[DIRECTORY]]
.SS DESCRIPTION
.PP
Apply pre\-aggregation recommendations to model YAML files.
.PP
Analyzes query patterns and automatically adds pre\-aggregation definitions to model YAML files.
.PP
Examples: sidemantic preagg apply models/ \-\-connection "bigquery://project/dataset" sidemantic preagg apply models/ \-\-db data.db \-\-top 5 sidemantic preagg apply models/ \-\-queries queries.sql \-\-dry\-run
.SS OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-queries, \-q PATH\fR
Path to file/folder with SQL queries
.TP
\fB\-\-connection TEXT\fR
Database connection string to fetch query history
.TP
\fB\-\-db PATH\fR
Path to DuckDB database file (shorthand for duckdb:/// connection)
.TP
\fB\-\-days, \-d INTEGER\fR
Days of query history to fetch (default: 7)
.TP
\fB\-\-limit, \-l INTEGER\fR
Max queries to analyze (default: 1000)
.TP
\fB\-\-min\-count INTEGER\fR
Minimum query count for recommendation (default: 10)
.TP
\fB\-\-min\-score FLOAT\fR
Minimum benefit score (0\-1, default: 0.3)
.TP
\fB\-\-top, \-n INTEGER\fR
Apply only top N recommendations
.TP
\fB\-\-dry\-run\fR
Show what would be added without writing files
.TP
\fB\-\-json\fR
Emit the apply report as JSON
.SH "SIDEMANTIC PREAGG REFRESH"
.SS SYNOPSIS
.B
sidemantic preagg refresh [OPTIONS] [[DIRECTORY]]
.SS DESCRIPTION
.PP
Refresh pre\-aggregation tables.
.PP
Generates materialization SQL for pre\-aggregations and executes refresh. Stateless: watermarks derived from existing tables. Use cron/Airflow for scheduling.
.PP
Examples: sidemantic preagg refresh models/ \-\-db data.db sidemantic preagg refresh models/ \-\-model orders \-\-mode full sidemantic preagg refresh models/ \-\-connection "postgres://localhost:5432/db"
.SS OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-model TEXT\fR
Only refresh pre\-aggregations for this model
.TP
\fB\-\-preagg, \-p TEXT\fR
Only refresh this specific pre\-aggregation
.TP
\fB\-\-mode TEXT\fR
Refresh mode: auto, full, incremental, merge, or engine
.TP
\fB\-\-connection TEXT\fR
Database connection string (e.g., postgres://host/db, bigquery://project/dataset)
.TP
\fB\-\-db PATH\fR
Path to DuckDB database file (shorthand for duckdb:/// connection)
.TP
\fB\-\-json\fR
Emit the refresh report as JSON
